Pre-heat the oven to 220 degrees. Wash the @potato{2} then chop lengthways into
wedges the thickness of your index finger. Toss in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and spread on a #baking tray{}. Cook on the top shelf of the oven until
crispy (around ~{25%minutes}).

Peel the outside green part of the @cucumber{1} off and discard. Peel strips of
the cucumber lengthways all the way round (you won't need the squidgy seeds in
the middle). Mix the cucumber with @salt{1/2%tsp} and leave in a #colander{} for
~{10%minutes}.

Chop your @carrot{1} into cubes less than ½cm in size. Peel and finely chop your
@onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Chop the @coriander{2}. Drain, rinse and
finely mash your @organic lentils{1} with a #fork{} in a #large bowl{}.

Heat @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the
onion and carrot and cook for ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the @red Thai style curry paste{3%tsp} and fry for another ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat.

Mix the onion and carrot through the lentils. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{1}, chopped
coriander, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a few good grinds of @black pepper{}. Toss everything
together. Divide the mixture between 2 equal portions and gently form into burger
patties.

> If your appetite allows it, place the patties in the fridge for 10 mins before
> frying. This will help the mixture stay together.

Squeeze the moisture out of the cucumber (preferably between a few sheets of
#kitchen towel{}). Then mix together with @Greek style natural yoghurt{2%tbsp}
and a few grinds of @pepper{}. Split your @brioche bun{2} in half. Put a frying
pan on medium-high heat. Toast the buns for a couple of mins on each side and
then remove.

In your (now empty) frying pan, add @olive oil{1%tbsp} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, cook the patties for ~{3%minutes} on both sides, or until golden and
heated through.

> Don't prod and poke the patties or they could break and be sure to cook them
> completely on one side before turning over.

To serve, top your buns with @wild rocket{1}, patties and the cucumber relish.
Serve your potato wedges on the side and tuck in.